          %blockquote
            %span.card-title.white-text Faith Onyebujoh
          %i.material-icons.right close
          %p.white-text Awarded the most outstanding youth in media and journalism by the NIGERIA Youth Merit Award in partnership with United Nations Youth Association and World Association of Youth, Faith was also acknowledged and given the "True Diva" award by the Men's Room publication.
          %p.white-text Popularly known as Faithelicious, she was born on the 25th of May and hails from delta state in Nigeria. She is a graduate of Geography and remote sensing from the Federal University of Technology Minna.
          %p.white-text Her principle in life is simplicity and decency. She loves swimming, watching movies, reading, meeting people and likes to believe the best in people. She loves music and is a great dancer.
          %p.white-text Having handled the love zone and the request show on Cool FM and for a brief period the midday dialogue on Nigeria Info in Lagos, she also co-produced the Enugu version "Wetin Dey" program of BBC World Service Trust.
          %p.white-text She has interviewed celebrities, politicians, entrepreneurs and professionals in various fields and this has helped her build strong speaking and communications skills.
          %p.white-text Ese had her first radio experience on her show where she was her regular guest on the women’s show called "Girl Talk."
          %p.white-text Faith is a breath of fresh air with a friendly smile, a lovely voice and a swell personality. She is currently one of the hosts of Femina Speaks TV and looking forward to joining other women in moving humanity forward.
          %p.white-text CONTACT FAITH:
          %p.white-text Twitter: @faithelicious
          %p.white-text Facebook: Faith Onyebujoh.
          %p.white-text Blog; www.memoirsofasoulsista.wordpress.com
